<item>
            <title>[LU-11544] interop: sanity-quota test 10 fails with &apos;set limit for root user successfully, expect failure&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11544</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity-quota test 10 started failing in interop testing on July 04, 2018 for the following combinations:&lt;br/&gt;
master, 2.11.52.82 and later, servers with&lt;br/&gt;
2.10.4 RC2 and later clients &lt;br/&gt;
2.11.0 clients &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the client test_log for &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/8b3d250a-cf0d-11e8-ad90-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/8b3d250a-cf0d-11e8-ad90-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt; , we see&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity-quota test 10: Test quota for root user ==================================================== 12:22:35 (1539433355)
Waiting for local destroys to complete
Creating test directory
CMD: onyx-45vm7,onyx-45vm8 lctl set_param fail_val=0 fail_loc=0
fail_val=0
fail_loc=0
fail_val=0
fail_loc=0
warning: inode softlimit is smaller than the miminal qunit size, please see the help of setquota or Lustre manual for details.
 sanity-quota test_10: @@@@@@ FAIL: set limit for root user successfully, expect failure
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Based on the starting date of this failure, I think the cause of this issue is that the patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7816&quot; title=&quot;Add default quota setting support for Lustre&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7816&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7816&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/32306&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/32306&lt;/a&gt; , has not landed to the b2_10 and b2_11 branches. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Logs for this failure can be found at&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/d0934eba-7fb0-11e8-b441-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/d0934eba-7fb0-11e8-b441-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/84564b96-9582-11e8-b0aa-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/84564b96-9582-11e8-b0aa-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/af4c42d6-97dc-11e8-87f3-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/af4c42d6-97dc-11e8-87f3-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/5de84b06-ce32-11e8-ad90-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/5de84b06-ce32-11e8-ad90-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Interop testing between master (2.12) servers and b2_10 or b2_11 clients</environment>
